text: Jean-Laurent Cochet (28 January 1935 – 7 April 2020) was a French actor and director. He is known for his roles in A Thousand Billion Dollars (1982) and Fort Saganne (1984). He was born in Romainville, Seine-Saint-Denis. On 7 April 2020, during the 2019–20 coronavirus pandemic, Cochet died on COVID-19 in Paris.
